<p>Incels hypocritically lament the ways these hierarchies harm them even while they subscribe to their valorization of certain kinds of bodies: the rich, thin, white women they call â€œStacys.â€ Srinivasan thinks that we can take inspiration instead from queer and Black women who have asked us to critically interrogate who and how we desire. For Srinivasan, this isnâ€™t about repressionÂ â€”Â itâ€™s about openness to the forms of sex and love that are blocked by our current power structures.</p>

